openai:gpt-4.1.description: Smartest non-reasoning model. GPT-4.1 excels at instruction following and tool calling, with broad knowledge across domains. It features a 1M token context window, and low latency without a reasoning step.

openai:gpt-5-nano.description: Fastest, most cost-efficient version of GPT-5. It's great for summarization and classification tasks.

openai:o3-deep-research.description: o3-deep-research is our most advanced model for deep research, designed to tackle complex, multi-step research tasks. It can search and synthesize information from across the internet as well as from your own data—brought in through MCP connectors.

openai:o4-mini-deep-research.description: o4-mini-deep-research is our faster, more affordable deep research model—ideal for tackling complex, multi-step research tasks. It can search and synthesize information from across the internet as well as from your own data, brought in through MCP connectors.

openai:gpt-5-mini-2025-08-07.description: GPT-5 mini is a faster, more cost-efficient version of GPT-5. It's great for well-defined tasks and precise prompts.

openai:gpt-5-2025-08-07.description: GPT-5 is our flagship model for coding, reasoning, and agentic tasks across domains.

openai:gpt-5.description: GPT-5 is our flagship model for coding, reasoning, and agentic tasks across domains.
